### 4. LOOKUP OPTIONS AND THEIR USAGE

**Option Flags** (LookupOptions.cs, lines 21-113):

| Flag | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `NamespaceAliasesOnly` | Only alias symbols |
| `NamespacesOrTypesOnly` | Filter for types/namespaces |
| `MustBeInvocableIfMember` | Only if method/event or delegate-type field/property |
| `MustBeInstance` | Instance members only |
| `MustNotBeInstance` | Static members only |
| `MustNotBeNamespace` | Exclude namespaces |
| `AllMethodsOnArityZero` | Consider generic methods even if arity=0 |
| `LabelsOnly` | Label lookup only (exclusive) |
| `UseBaseReferenceAccessibility` | Use base.X accessibility rules |
| `IncludeExtensionMethods` | Include extension methods |
| `AttributeTypeOnly` | Attribute type lookup (with "Attribute" suffix) |
| `VerbatimNameAttributeTypeOnly` | Attribute lookup without suffix |
| `AllNamedTypesOnArityZero` | Consider generic types even if arity=0 |
| `MustNotBeMethodTypeParameter` | Exclude method type parameters |
| `MustBeAbstractOrVirtual` | Abstract or virtual only |
| `MustNotBeParameter` | Exclude parameters |

**Option Filtering in `CheckViability()`** (lines 1385-1538):

Early filters apply options to validate symbols:

```csharp
// Accessibility wrapper
if ((options & LookupOptions.MustNotBeParameter) != 0 && unwrappedSymbol is ParameterSymbol)
    return LookupResult.Empty();

// Type filtering
if ((options & LookupOptions.NamespacesOrTypesOnly) != 0 && !(unwrappedSymbol is NamespaceOrTypeSymbol))
